00:16:36.080 --> 00:16:38.590 align:middle line:10%
That is difficult.
It is very hard

00:16:38.590 --> 00:16:44.130 align:middle line:10%
to convince somebody to take
on a different worldview.

00:16:44.130 --> 00:16:47.750 align:middle line:84%
Many years ago, I had this
conversation with Bob Jahn,

00:16:47.750 --> 00:16:50.100 align:middle line:90%
and we talked about this.

00:16:50.100 --> 00:16:53.970 align:middle line:84%
And I said, given
human nature, given

00:16:53.970 --> 00:16:57.750 align:middle line:84%
its greedy, self-serving
style of being,

00:16:57.750 --> 00:17:02.550 align:middle line:84%
how are you ever going to
convince these people to love?

00:17:02.550 --> 00:17:04.079 align:middle line:84%
From the beginning
of time, there

00:17:04.079 --> 00:17:05.520 align:middle line:84%
have been these
great teachers who

00:17:05.520 --> 00:17:08.790 align:middle line:84%
have come along and preached
how we should love one another,

00:17:08.790 --> 00:17:11.099 align:middle line:90%
and what good has it done?

00:17:11.099 --> 00:17:13.869 align:middle line:84%
And Bob said something I
think was very profound.

00:17:13.869 --> 00:17:16.109 align:middle line:84%
He said, the only
way you're going

00:17:16.109 --> 00:17:19.380 align:middle line:84%
to get people to love one
another is when you can

00:17:19.380 --> 00:17:23.819 align:middle line:84%
persuade them that it's in their
own greedy, self-serving best

00:17:23.819 --> 00:17:26.010 align:middle line:90%
interest to do so.

00:17:26.010 --> 00:17:29.250 align:middle line:84%
They need to recognize
that if they don't do it,

00:17:29.250 --> 00:17:31.140 align:middle line:90%
they're in deep trouble.

00:17:31.140 --> 00:17:33.070 align:middle line:90%
You do it because you have to.

00:17:33.070 --> 00:17:36.270 align:middle line:84%
You do it because it's the
only option you've got left.

00:17:36.270 --> 00:17:39.060 align:middle line:84%
When the despair
becomes so great,

00:17:39.060 --> 00:17:41.610 align:middle line:84%
either you're going to
get depressed and end up

00:17:41.610 --> 00:17:43.770 align:middle line:84%
committing suicide,
or you're going

00:17:43.770 --> 00:17:46.380 align:middle line:84%
to have some kind
of an epiphany,

00:17:46.380 --> 00:17:50.650 align:middle line:84%
some kind of an insight
that suddenly white light,

00:17:50.650 --> 00:17:52.800 align:middle line:90%
and you go, oh.

00:17:52.800 --> 00:17:55.140 align:middle line:84%
I remember a story
a friend of mine

00:17:55.140 --> 00:17:58.770 align:middle line:84%
told of her father who had
been a career Marine, this very

00:17:58.770 --> 00:18:02.370 align:middle line:84%
serious old guy,
but he was dying.

00:18:02.370 --> 00:18:05.640 align:middle line:84%
She was sitting at his
bedside, holding his hand.

00:18:05.640 --> 00:18:06.900 align:middle line:90%
He was asleep.

00:18:06.900 --> 00:18:09.090 align:middle line:84%
And at one point,
he opened his eyes,

00:18:09.090 --> 00:18:11.700 align:middle line:90%
and he looked at her very alert.

00:18:11.700 --> 00:18:13.650 align:middle line:90%
And he said, you know what?

00:18:13.650 --> 00:18:16.690 align:middle line:90%
It's all about love, isn't it?

00:18:16.690 --> 00:18:18.810 align:middle line:90%
And it has to come like that.

00:18:18.810 --> 00:18:20.370 align:middle line:90%
You can't tell people that.

00:18:20.370 --> 00:18:23.130 align:middle line:90%
You can't preach it to them.

00:18:23.130 --> 00:18:27.030 align:middle line:84%
In my own experience, it
was that kind of a thing.

00:18:27.030 --> 00:18:28.750 align:middle line:90%
I was very depressed.

00:18:28.750 --> 00:18:31.440 align:middle line:84%
I was a very unhappy
young person.

00:18:31.440 --> 00:18:34.760 align:middle line:84%
I just felt that nothing
was going to happen.

00:18:34.760 --> 00:18:38.430 align:middle line:84%
I had spent my life trying
to please other people.

00:18:38.430 --> 00:18:42.090 align:middle line:84%
And no matter how hard I tried,
I wasn't able to please them.

00:18:42.090 --> 00:18:43.780 align:middle line:90%
They were always critical.

00:18:43.780 --> 00:18:47.520 align:middle line:84%
And then I had this
sudden insight that said,

00:18:47.520 --> 00:18:50.250 align:middle line:84%
you've got to stop trying
to please other people.

00:18:50.250 --> 00:18:54.540 align:middle line:84%
Because even if you
do, it's not you

00:18:54.540 --> 00:18:56.790 align:middle line:90%
that they're going to accept.

00:18:56.790 --> 00:19:00.360 align:middle line:84%
They're accepting that false
face that you're putting on,

00:19:00.360 --> 00:19:02.550 align:middle line:84%
and that's not going
to make you happy.

00:19:02.550 --> 00:19:06.060 align:middle line:84%
Wouldn't you be better off
just being who you really are?

00:19:06.060 --> 00:19:08.610 align:middle line:84%
And then if people don't like
you, they don't like you.

00:19:08.610 --> 00:19:13.160 align:middle line:84%
But the people who do
like you really like you.

00:19:13.160 --> 00:19:16.570 align:middle line:84%
We spend so much of
our lives reacting

00:19:16.570 --> 00:19:21.430 align:middle line:84%
to this terrorizing threat
of what will people think.

00:19:21.430 --> 00:19:26.170 align:middle line:84%
But pleasing somebody by
being false is not love,

00:19:26.170 --> 00:19:29.410 align:middle line:84%
and demanding that somebody
behave a certain way

00:19:29.410 --> 00:19:31.960 align:middle line:84%
so you would love them,
that's not love either.

00:19:31.960 --> 00:19:36.280 align:middle line:84%
Love is being who you are
and accepting other people

00:19:36.280 --> 00:19:38.200 align:middle line:90%
for who they are.

00:19:38.200 --> 00:19:39.800 align:middle line:90%
How do you get there?

00:19:39.800 --> 00:19:42.160 align:middle line:90%
I don't know.

00:19:42.160 --> 00:19:46.480 align:middle line:84%
There were days when I find the
circumstances in our society

00:19:46.480 --> 00:19:47.890 align:middle line:90%
terrifying.

00:19:47.890 --> 00:19:51.610 align:middle line:84%
Other days, I find
it hilariously funny.

00:19:51.610 --> 00:19:54.160 align:middle line:84%
It's so bad that
it's really funny.

00:19:54.160 --> 00:19:56.320 align:middle line:84%
There's a part of us
that is destructive,

00:19:56.320 --> 00:19:59.530 align:middle line:84%
that wants to break things
down and create chaos.

00:19:59.530 --> 00:20:01.360 align:middle line:84%
And there is a part
of us that wants

00:20:01.360 --> 00:20:05.470 align:middle line:84%
to be drawn together, to
be part of a social group,

00:20:05.470 --> 00:20:10.360 align:middle line:84%
to be in love, to be
part of something bigger.

00:20:10.360 --> 00:20:13.270 align:middle line:84%
We have to choose which
path we're going to follow.

00:20:13.270 --> 00:20:16.510 align:middle line:84%
They're both there
potentially, and we're all

00:20:16.510 --> 00:20:19.120 align:middle line:84%
going to have days when we
go this way and days when

00:20:19.120 --> 00:20:20.470 align:middle line:90%
we go that way.

00:20:20.470 --> 00:20:23.500 align:middle line:84%
But at some level,
we have to choose

00:20:23.500 --> 00:20:26.890 align:middle line:84%
which path we're going
to make a commitment to.

00:20:26.890 --> 00:20:28.390 align:middle line:90%
What does that?

00:20:28.390 --> 00:20:33.730 align:middle line:84%
What is it within us that makes
us choose which path to follow?

00:20:33.730 --> 00:20:34.990 align:middle line:90%
I don't know.

00:20:34.990 --> 00:20:36.910 align:middle line:84%
But I think we do
have free will.

00:20:36.910 --> 00:20:40.180 align:middle line:90%
I think we can choose.

00:20:40.180 --> 00:20:44.440 align:middle line:84%
I mentioned earlier, I had
a very unpleasant childhood.

00:20:44.440 --> 00:20:47.680 align:middle line:90%
OK, I was not a happy kid.

00:20:47.680 --> 00:20:51.370 align:middle line:84%
I know people who
have had experiences,

00:20:51.370 --> 00:20:56.200 align:middle line:84%
early experiences akin to what
I had and they become bitter.

00:20:56.200 --> 00:20:59.860 align:middle line:84%
They become angry, resentful,
and they carry that pain

00:20:59.860 --> 00:21:02.900 align:middle line:90%
with them all their lives.

00:21:02.900 --> 00:21:03.700 align:middle line:90%
I didn't.

00:21:03.700 --> 00:21:06.070 align:middle line:84%
I kind of got out of it
and decided this is not

00:21:06.070 --> 00:21:07.840 align:middle line:90%
a very productive way to go.

00:21:07.840 --> 00:21:11.410 align:middle line:84%
I'm not hurting
anybody but myself.

00:21:11.410 --> 00:21:14.200 align:middle line:84%
We're not going to be
able to love others

00:21:14.200 --> 00:21:17.320 align:middle line:84%
until we can love
ourselves, and we're not

00:21:17.320 --> 00:21:18.800 align:middle line:90%
taught to love ourselves.

00:21:18.800 --> 00:21:21.280 align:middle line:84%
We're taught to be
critical of ourselves.

00:21:21.280 --> 00:21:22.570 align:middle line:90%
We're taught to compete.

00:21:22.570 --> 00:21:26.500 align:middle line:84%
We're taught to live up to
other people's-- we don't love

00:21:26.500 --> 00:21:27.640 align:middle line:90%
ourselves.

00:21:27.640 --> 00:21:29.200 align:middle line:84%
And we're not going
to love ourselves

00:21:29.200 --> 00:21:31.700 align:middle line:84%
until we accept ourselves
for who we are and say, hey,

00:21:31.700 --> 00:21:33.420 align:middle line:90%
it's OK.

00:21:33.420 --> 00:21:37.050 align:middle line:84%
I may not be
perfect, but I'm me.

00:21:37.050 --> 00:21:42.060 align:middle line:84%
My colleague, Robert Jahn passed
away almost two years ago.

00:21:42.060 --> 00:21:45.100 align:middle line:84%
His brain is no
longer functioning,

00:21:45.100 --> 00:21:47.320 align:middle line:90%
but I feel his presence.

00:21:47.320 --> 00:21:51.750 align:middle line:84%
I feel his consciousness
because we were so close.

00:21:51.750 --> 00:21:52.740 align:middle line:90%
We worked together.

00:21:52.740 --> 00:21:54.610 align:middle line:90%
We understood each other.

00:21:54.610 --> 00:21:57.690 align:middle line:84%
We had such an intense
dynamic for so long.

00:21:57.690 --> 00:22:00.570 align:middle line:84%
I know his consciousness
is still there,

00:22:00.570 --> 00:22:03.090 align:middle line:84%
and there are times
when I have a thought,

00:22:03.090 --> 00:22:06.360 align:middle line:84%
and I get a sense of,
no, that's not right,

00:22:06.360 --> 00:22:09.360 align:middle line:84%
and I know it's
Bob talking to me.

00:22:09.360 --> 00:22:13.350 align:middle line:84%
There's a lot of evidence
that consciousness is not over

00:22:13.350 --> 00:22:15.330 align:middle line:90%
just because the body is.

00:22:15.330 --> 00:22:18.240 align:middle line:84%
And there's no way you're
going to convince people

00:22:18.240 --> 00:22:21.390 align:middle line:84%
who are skeptical of it,
and I don't feel the need

00:22:21.390 --> 00:22:23.492 align:middle line:90%
to try to convince them.

00:22:23.492 --> 00:22:26.860 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:22:26.860 --> 00:22:31.240 align:middle line:84%
We are expressions
of the life force.

00:22:31.240 --> 00:22:36.700 align:middle line:84%
We are the manifestation of this
dynamic between consciousness

00:22:36.700 --> 00:22:41.890 align:middle line:84%
and potentiality, the universe
wanting to experience itself.

00:22:41.890 --> 00:22:46.090 align:middle line:84%
There's something precious
about being a part of the whole

00:22:46.090 --> 00:22:48.430 align:middle line:84%
and recognizing that
there is a whole.

00:22:48.430 --> 00:22:50.650 align:middle line:90%
I'm not here all alone.

00:22:50.650 --> 00:22:54.220 align:middle line:84%
I'm not just here without some
purpose, or why am I here.

00:22:54.220 --> 00:22:55.052 align:middle line:90%
Who am I?

00:22:55.052 --> 00:22:56.260 align:middle line:90%
What difference does it make?

00:22:56.260 --> 00:22:58.720 align:middle line:90%
Maybe I should shoot myself.

00:22:58.720 --> 00:23:01.330 align:middle line:84%
No, I have a purpose
to serve and that

00:23:01.330 --> 00:23:06.070 align:middle line:84%
is to contribute in whatever
way I can to this whole.

00:23:06.070 --> 00:23:09.220 align:middle line:84%
To be as good a
little cell as I can

00:23:09.220 --> 00:23:12.400 align:middle line:84%
be because that will
enhance the health

00:23:12.400 --> 00:23:15.340 align:middle line:84%
of the big organism
in some way even

00:23:15.340 --> 00:23:18.520 align:middle line:90%
though I don't understand it.

00:23:18.520 --> 00:23:21.370 align:middle line:84%
Where people get into a
different state of mind,

00:23:21.370 --> 00:23:26.020 align:middle line:84%
and suddenly they see that
everything's really connected.

00:23:26.020 --> 00:23:27.940 align:middle line:90%
It isn't all separate pieces.

00:23:27.940 --> 00:23:30.790 align:middle line:90%
It's all one big unit.

00:23:30.790 --> 00:23:33.400 align:middle line:84%
You just realize that
you're just one little piece

00:23:33.400 --> 00:23:37.030 align:middle line:84%
of the whole, and all of
the pieces are connected,

00:23:37.030 --> 00:23:38.830 align:middle line:90%
and it's beautiful.

00:23:38.830 --> 00:23:41.320 align:middle line:84%
It gives you such a
wonderful warm feeling

00:23:41.320 --> 00:23:44.530 align:middle line:90%
of purpose and meaning.

00:23:44.530 --> 00:23:46.480 align:middle line:90%
It doesn't last very long.

00:23:46.480 --> 00:23:49.150 align:middle line:84%
You usually come back down
to Earth, so to speak,

00:23:49.150 --> 00:23:52.390 align:middle line:84%
and you remember that you've
got to go to the grocery store

00:23:52.390 --> 00:23:55.210 align:middle line:84%
or you've got to
go wash the dishes.

00:23:55.210 --> 00:23:58.180 align:middle line:84%
But it carries back
with you some harmony,

00:23:58.180 --> 00:24:01.850 align:middle line:84%
some piece of that that
says, I had that experience.

00:24:01.850 --> 00:24:03.710 align:middle line:90%
I don't have to doubt it.

00:24:03.710 --> 00:24:05.650 align:middle line:84%
I don't have to worry
about somebody else

00:24:05.650 --> 00:24:07.990 align:middle line:84%
or depend on someone
else describing it.

00:24:07.990 --> 00:24:11.200 align:middle line:84%
I've seen it, I've known
it, and I know it's real.

00:24:11.200 --> 00:24:14.850 align:middle line:90%
